    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "S",
        "section_value": "The patient reports intermittent left back pain, described as sharp or moving, and occasionally non-existent. He reports no current fever or other systemic symptoms. He denies recent trauma. He states he has not noticed any increased tiredness or appetite changes. He reports increased urine output, particularly at night, and has been drinking more water. He denies any sick contacts at home or school. His brother smokes and has been told not to smoke, but he does not listen. The patient reports four strep infections in the last five months, attributing them to his doctor's diagnosis.",
