      },
      {
        "heading": "O",
        "section_value": "Physical exam reveals no tenderness to palpation of the back, no cervical lymphadenopathy, lungs are clear to auscultation, heart sounds are normal without murmurs, and abdominal exam is unremarkable. Throat exam shows no erythema or swelling, tonsils are midline and unremarkable. Vital signs are within normal limits.",
        "medical_concepts": [
          "back tenderness",
          "cervical lymphadenopathy",
          "lung auscultation",
          "heart sounds",
          "heart murmur",
          "abdominal exam",
          "throat erythema",
