        ]
      },
      {
        "heading": "A",
        "section_value": "The patient's symptoms are concerning for possible glomerular nephritis, potentially related to recurrent strep infections. A CT scan revealed findings suggestive of glomerular nephritis. Referral to an ENT specialist is indicated to consider tonsillectomy. Further investigation is needed to determine the underlying cause of the recurrent strep infections.",
        "medical_concepts": [
          "glomerular nephritis",
          "recurrent strep infections",
          "CT scan",
          "ENT specialist",
          "tonsillectomy"
        ]
      },
      {
        "heading": "P",
        "section_value": "Order a lipid panel, UA, CMP, CBC, vitamin D, and TSH. Refer to an ENT specialist for evaluation and consideration of tonsillectomy. Schedule a follow-up appointment in one week to review lab results and discuss further management. Advise the patient to return if symptoms worsen or do not improve. Offer to discuss free food options at the restaurant if infection control is improved.",
        "medical_concepts": [
